    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="36" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 808.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 12, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 3d of December last
                            (No. 547) has been received, together with the copy of the
                            correspondence which, at that date, had taken place between yourself and
                            Earl Russell on the subject of the Rappahannock. I have the pleasure of
                            informing you that not only your proceedings mentioned in the despatch,
                            but also the views and suggestions therein contained, in regard to a
                            just treatment of the case of the Rappahannock, and kindred subjects,
                            are approved by the President.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles F. Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
